==Translingual==
[[File:Pallid Carrier Shell - Xenophora pallidula (3730748447).jpg|right|thumb|{{taxlink|Xenophora pallidula|species|'''Xenophora''' pallidula}}]]
===Etymology===
{{confix|mul|xeno-|-phora}}
Coined in 1807 by {{w|Gotthelf Fischer von Waldheim}} from {{m|grc|ξένος||strange/foreign or stranger/foreigner/guest}} + {{m|grc|φορά||carrying or burden}}: they attach foreign objects to their shells, including other shells.
